# Nick Fury — Mission Log: Story 1

Intelligence flagged an anomalous energy signature off the Norwegian
coast. Cross-referencing SHIELD archives, I identified it as a
decommissioned HYDRA submarine base we thought was destroyed in 1998.
It wasn't.

I assessed the situation: one target, underwater, minimal footprint
required. No need for a full team. I assigned Stark — fastest breach,
cleanest extraction, and if anyone can crack a HYDRA mainframe solo
underwater at 2,300 feet, it's him.

I monitored the operation from the helicarrier. Stark was in and out
in under 8 minutes. We recovered 4.7TB of HYDRA operational data —
sleeper agent coordinates, active cells, pending ops across 11
countries.

This changes the board significantly. I am already briefing the
World Security Council.

Stark's debrief was insufferable as usual. The results were not.
